    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2797728047" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13251473867681479267">By now, you expect Isabel to interfere with just about anything she runs across. So in this installment it&apos;s fun to see her hold back when it comes to love of her own and someone else&apos;s. <br/><br/>Finally... the build up for the two has been getting to the point of were they not to get together there was something wrong and the story becomes less believable. Isabel acts slow due to over thinking things over much and this can make her seem fuddy duddy for her early forties age. <br/><br/>This book was particularly g</span>
  <span id="freeText13251473867681479267" style="display:none">By now, you expect Isabel to interfere with just about anything she runs across. So in this installment it's fun to see her hold back when it comes to love of her own and someone else's. <br /><br />Finally... the build up for the two has been getting to the point of were they not to get together there was something wrong and the story becomes less believable. Isabel acts slow due to over thinking things over much and this can make her seem fuddy duddy for her early forties age. <br /><br />This book was particularly good because she didn't have to go out of her way as much as she did in the first two books to find the philosophical dilemma. She is less meddling than being called for an opinion. There is a nice conclusion to the two couples of interest and change. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13251473867681479267" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

